items.abstract: <jats:p>A new procedure is described for the synthesis of α,β-glycosyl cyanides by the reaction of per-O-benzylated S-α-ᴅ-glycopyranosyl phosphorothioates with trimethylsilyl cyanide in the presence of Lewis acid. Starting S-glycosyl phosphorothioates are prepared, directly, from O-benzyl protected reducing D-hexopyranoses (gluco-, galacto-, manno-) and alkylammonium salt of phosphorothioic acid under Lewis acid catalysis.</jats:p>
